## 3. Code Quality & Performance Optimization Findings

While writing tests, we identified a critical performance concern in [AdminService.java](file:///c:/TRAINING/TalentTrade-Skill-Exchange-Platform/src/main/java/com/talenttrade/service/AdminService.java):

> [!WARNING]
> **Severe Memory & Database Bottlenecks in Dashboard Statistics**
> - In `getDashboardSummary()`, the service executes `.findAll().stream().filter(...)` repeatedly on `exchangeRequestRepository`, `sessionRepository`, and `notificationRepository` (e.g. lines 52-54, 59-61, and 70).
> - In `getPlatformAnalytics()`, the service loads all users, user skills, exchange requests, sessions, and reviews (lines 79-83) completely into application heap memory.
> - **Recommendation**: Replace all `.findAll().stream()` aggregates with database-level counts and customized projections (e.g. using `countByStatus(RequestStatus status)` or JQL queries with GROUP BY). This offloads memory processing to the database index level.
